  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Based on the ZPD, we reflect on our understanding of the current affordances of ChatGPT to help us articulate the different aspects of PL which can be supported.",
    "ZPD refers to the difference between what a learner can do without help and what they can achieve with guidance and encouragement from a skilled partner (Vygotsky, 1978).",
    "Central to Vygotsky's theory of cognitive development, the ZPD delineates the difference between what a learner can achieve independently and what they can accomplish with the guidance or collaboration of a more knowledgeable other (Vygotsky, 1978).",
    "This zone represents the potential for learning, emphasizing the importance of social interaction and scaffolding in the educational process.",
    "Within the ZPD, learners are provided with support that is gradually withdrawn as they gain mastery, promoting a transition from assisted to independent problemsolving."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
